rised of descriptive chapters, broken into the following subsets: Eurasia, South- East Asia and Oceania, Australia-New Guinea, Africa, North America and South America.The Handbook features 3 separate indexes detailing languages, names, subjects."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxMorphology. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAgbedor, Paul Kofi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAgbetsoamedo, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmery, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArbaoui, Nora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArcodia, Giorgio Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArdakani, Negar Davari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArtiagoitia, Xabier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArvin, Mahdiye, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarbaresi, Lavinia Merlini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerg, René van den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernal, Elisenda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirioukova, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowler, Margit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCahill, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampos, Guillermo González, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChang, Hui-Huan Ann, 